Robert F Tobler <rft@raven.cg.tuwien.ac.at> wrote:

> Since I like the zsh very much, I hope you can fix this problem.

Try:

d0|vt100|vt100-am|vt100am|Digital VT100:\
        :cr=^M:nl=^J:bl=^G:ta=^I:\
        :do=^J:co#80:li#24:cl=50\E[;H\E[2J:sf=2*\ED:\
        :le=^H:bs:am:cm=5\E[%i%d;%dH:nd=2\E[C:up=2\E[A:\
        :ce=3\E[K:cd=50\E[J:so=2\E[7m:se=2\E[m:us=2\E[4m:ue=2\E[m:\
        :md=2\E[1m:mr=2\E[7m:mb=2\E[5m:me=2\E[m:is=\E[1;24r\E[24;1H:\
        :ct=2\E[3g:st=2\EH:\
        :rf=/usr/share/lib/tabset/vt100:\
        :rs=\E>\E[?3l\E[?4l\E[?5l\E[?7h\E[?8h:ks=\E[?1h:ke=\E[?1l:\
        :ku=\EOA:kd=\EOB:kr=\EOC:kl=\EOD:kb=^H:\
        :ho=\E[H:k1=\EOP:k2=\EOQ:k3=\EOR:k4=\EOS:pt:sr=2*\EM:vt#3:xn:\
        :sc=\E7:rc=\E8:cs=\E[%i%d;%dr:\
        :it#8:xo:

This one seems to work, I haven't testet it too intensively though,
please tell us your results.

(Probably rf needs be changed into ":rf=/usr/lib/tabset/vt100:")

Wolfgang.

